\pard\f0\fs28 Annual or perennial herbs or small shrubs up to 100 cm, sometimes with latex. Stems erect, trailing or twining. Leaves simple, usually entire. Flowers solitary or in terminal or axillary inflorescences; pedicels with 2 minute to leaf-like bracteoles. Corolla infundibuliform, glabrous except for five usually pubescent stripes often of a different colour. Stamens inserted at the base of the corolla-tube, included. Ovary 2-locular; stigma 2-lobed, the lobes filiform to cylindric-clavate. Capsule usually 4-seeded, 1- to 2-celled. Pollen grains tricolpate; exine not spinose.
